text: This is a list of dinosaurs whose remains have been found in Asia, other than India. During the Mesozoic, India was not part of Asia. It was part of the supercontinent Gondwana, and then a separate island. More dinosaurs have been found in Asia than any other continent so far. : Name Period DietDiet is sometimes hard to determine for dinosaurs and should be considered a "best guess" Notes Abrosaurus Jurassic herbivore A Small sauropod that looked a lot like Camarasaurus.
